lead_paragraph: After a vote count that dragged on for more than two weeks, Representative Robert K. Dornan, the most blusterous Republican conservative on Capitol Hill, finally went down to defeat today, narrowly vanquished in his bid for a 10th term by a liberal Democrat and political novice, Loretta Sanchez. The contest for California's 46th District seat, in the heart of Orange County, was decided by just 984 of the 94,944 votes cast, and the outcome was taken by political experts as striking evidence of the sharp growth of Hispanic political power in the country.
abstract: Final count in California's 46th Congressional District gives Loretta Sanchez, a liberal Democratic novice, a narrow victory over Rep Robert K Dornan; Dornan will protest count; election provides striking evidence of sharp growth of Hispanic political power (S)

headline.main: 2 Weeks After Election, Dornan Loses Seat
